{"title":"Pro bike: Remco Evenepoel’s rainbow Specialized S-Works Tarmac SL7 from Liège-Bastogne-Liège","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/remco-evenepoel-specialized-sworks-tarmac-sl7-bike","date":1682411129000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/remco-evenepoel-specialized-sworks-tarmac-sl7-bike\">Pro bike: Remco Evenepoel’s rainbow Specialized S-Works Tarmac SL7 from Liège-Bastogne-Liège</a></p>\n\n<p>And the award for easiest Monument win of all time goes to <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/remco-evenepoel\" target=\"_blank\">Remco Evenepoel</a>. <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/soudal-quickstep\" target=\"_blank\">Soudal-QuickStep’s</a> World Champion breezed his way to a second successive Liège-Bastogne-Liège win, barely breathing as the rest of the field battled for second place.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Young Remco was hot off an altitude camp as part of his preparation for the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\" target=\"_blank\">Giro d’Italia</a>, where he will rekindle his budding rivalry with Primož Roglič in the fight for the <em><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-d-italia-why-jersey-pink\" target=\"_blank\">maglia rosa</a>. </em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Of course as part of the Wolfpack he was riding <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/specialized-tarmac-sl7-review-end-of-the-venge\" target=\"_blank\">Specialized’s S-Works Tarmac SL7</a> – as was fellow Liège winner <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/2023-pro-cycling-liege-bastogne\" target=\"_blank\">Demi Vollering</a>, congrats to Specialized for the sweep – with his frame in world championship livery, to match his white shorts, which were more of a ballsy choice.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some nice close-ups of Evenepoel’s bike courtesy of Soudal-QuickStep, who said they were having a bad Classics season?</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h3><span>Related Posts</span></h3>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/2023-pro-cycling-liege-bastogne\">Pro Log: Demi Vollering’s historic Ardennes triple, Tadej Pogačar’s injury update, creepy AI Jonas Vingegaard and Vuelta a España’s official song</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/specialized-tarmac-sl7-review-end-of-the-venge\">Specialized Tarmac SL7 review</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pinarello-dogma-f-ineos-pidcock-bike\">Tour de France bikes: Tom Pidcock’s Pinarello Dogma F</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"728\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-3-728x970.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-3-728x970.jpg 728w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-3-225x300.jpg 225w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-3-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-3-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-3-1536x2048.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-3-750x1000.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-3-1140x1520.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-3.jpg 1920w\" /><figcaption>Soudal-QuickStep</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>He’s certainly making the most of the rainbow, fair play to him.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"728\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-4-728x970.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-4-728x970.jpg 728w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-4-225x300.jpg 225w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-4-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-4-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-4-1536x2048.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-4-750x1000.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-4-1140x1520.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-4.jpg 1920w\" /><figcaption>Soudal-QuickStep</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It helps when the best riders crash out before TV coverage starts, or only ride the cobbled Classics, but Evenepoel would’ve fancied his chances against Tadej Pogačar, Mathieu van der Poel and Wout van Aert if they’d have been there in the finale.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"728\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-2-728x970.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-2-728x970.jpg 728w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-2-225x300.jpg 225w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-2-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-2-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-2-1536x2048.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-2-750x1000.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-2-1140x1520.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-2.jpg 1920w\" /><figcaption>Soudal-QuickStep</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Keep your eyes peeled, it’s almost three years since Specialized released the SL7, so it’s about time for an SL8.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"728\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-1-728x970.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-1-728x970.jpg 728w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-1-225x300.jpg 225w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-1-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-1-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-1-1536x2048.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-1-750x1000.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-1-1140x1520.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/remco-evenepoel-s-works-tarmac-sl7-2023-1.jpg 1920w\" /><figcaption>Soudal-QuickStep</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Very classy.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Remco Evenepoel’s Specialized Tarmac SL7 spec</h3>\n\n\n\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Frameset</td><td>Specialized S-Works Tarmac SL7</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Levers</td><td>Shimano Dura-Ace R9200</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Brakes</td><td>Shimano Dura-Ace R9200</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Rear derailleur</td><td>Shimano Dura-Ace R9200</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Front derailleur</td><td>Shimano Dura-Ace R9200</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Crankset</td><td>Shimano Dura-Ace R9200</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Cassette</td><td>Shimano Dura-Ace R9200</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Chain</td><td>Shimano Dura-Ace R9200</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Wheels</td><td>Roval Rapide CLX II</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Tyres</td><td>Specialized Turbo Cotton</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Bar + stem</td><td>Roval Alpinist SL</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Seatpost</td><td>Specialized Carbon</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Saddle</td><td>Specialized Power Pro with Mirror</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Pedals</td><td>Shimano Dura-Ace R9100</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n\t<td>Accessories</td><td>Tacx bottle cages, Supacaz bar tape</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/remco-evenepoel-specialized-sworks-tarmac-sl7-bike\">Pro bike: Remco Evenepoel’s rainbow Specialized S-Works Tarmac SL7 from Liège-Bastogne-Liège